The paper deals with property testing of (di)graph properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of graph properties in bounded-degree models is a direction of research in property testing, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses directed and undirected graphs, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG).
